Day 2: Calculator
Create a new Python file in this package(Day2).
Use the input() function to ask the user for two numbers.
Store the input in variables and only allow numeric values to be entered.
Define functions for addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division that take two parameters (the user's input values).
Use the return keyword to return the result of each arithmetic operation.
Call each function with the user's input values and print the result using the print() function.
Run the program to make sure it works correctly.
